# Platform security (JOBBIE)

## Transport & headers

- Production: HTTPS only at CDN/LB; redirect HTTPâ†’HTTPS; HSTS on PWA and API responses.
- Nest: `helmet` in `main.ts`; PWA: security headers + CSP in `nuxt.config.ts` `nitro.routeRules`.
- CSP must allowlist Stripe, Turnstile, Supabase, Sentry, PostHog only when those integrations are enabled.

## Secrets

- Never commit `.env`, service role keys, `AUDIT_CHAIN_SECRET`, `SESSION_COOKIE_SECRET`, or Stripe secrets.
- All secrets via environment variables or host secret manager; document rotation in `docs/database-operations-runbook.md`.

## BFF session cookies (Nest API)

- Browserâ†’API auth: HttpOnly `jb_at` / `jb_sid` cookies set by `POST /api/auth/session` after Supabase login.
- Cookie flags in production: `Secure`, `SameSite=Lax` (or `Strict` if same-site only), `Path=/api`.
- CSRF: readable `jb_csrf` cookie + `X-CSRF-Token` header on `POST`/`PATCH`/`DELETE`; never ship cookie auth without CSRF.
- PWA `useApi()`: `credentials: 'include'`; do not send `Authorization: Bearer` to Nest after session bootstrap.
- Supabase Realtime/storage may use in-memory tokens only; do not persist access/refresh in `localStorage` for API.

## Auth & account risk

- Failed logins: `POST /api/auth/security/login-attempt` + `auth_security_events`; Turnstile on failures when configured.
- Admin routes (desktop `jobbie-admin/api`): `AppRoleGuard` + `@RequireRecentLogin()` on sensitive mutations.
- Sensitive mutations: `@RequireRecentLogin()` (step-up within 15 min) â€” billing, account delete, admin moderation, passkeys.
- Account enforcement: `profiles.account_status`; admin suspend via service role only; audit `account.suspended` / `account.unsuspended`.

## Abuse & audit

- User reports: `POST /api/reports` â†’ `content_reports` + audit event.
- Admin moderation and enforcement: `audit.recordAuditEvent` on every decision.
- Never grant `authenticated` DML on `audit_events`, `auth_security_events`, `login_attempt_counters`, `api_user_sessions`.

## Database

- Follow `.cursor/rules/database-engineering.mdc` and `supabase-rls.mdc` for new tables and grants.

